HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 405
BY REPRESENTATIVE BAYHAM
A RESOLUTION
To commend Paris Saint-Germain Football Club on winning its second consecutive UEFA
Champions League title.
WHEREAS, Paris Saint-Germain Football Club lifted the UEFA Champions League
Trophy for the second consecutive year after a 4-3 penalty shootout victory over Arsenal in
the final of the 2025-2026 Champions League at Puskas Arena in Budapest, Hungary; and
WHEREAS, Paris Saint-Germain Football Club, known by fans as Les Rouge-et-
Bleu, were cheered to victory by seventeen thousand fans in attendance at the game in
Budapest, and thousands more across France and the rest of the world; and
WHEREAS, with the addition of the 2026 UEFA Champions League Trophy, Paris
Saint-Germain has fifty-seven domestic and international titles in its trophy cabinet; it also
defended its French Ligue 1 title during the 2025-2026 season; and
WHEREAS, Paris Saint-Germain fielded the second-youngest squad during the
2025-2026 Champions League; the club relied on its incredible attacking depth and tied its
own record of seven players involved in at least five goals throughout the tournament; and
WHEREAS, Paris Saint-Germain Football Club is led by its president, Nasser Al-
Khelaïfi, and the men's team is managed by Luis Enrique; the team's goalkeepers are Matvei
Safonov, Lucas Chevalier, and Renato Marin; the defenders are Achraf Hakimi, Marquinhos,
Lucas Hernandez, Nuno Mendes, Lucas Beraldo, Illia Zabarnyi, and Willian Pacho; the
midfielders are Fabián Ruiz, Vitinha, Lee Kang-in, Senny Mayulu, Dro Fernández, Warren
Zaïre-Emery, and João Neves; and the forwards are Khvicha Kvaratskhelia, Gonçalo Ramos,
Ousmane Dembélé, Désiré Doué, Bradley Barcola, Quentin Ndjantou, and Ibrahim Mbaye;
and
